snippet.title: Hagwon interviews, possible questions, what to ask | Teaching in Korea: Episode 2
snippet.description:
Hi guys! Since the last video I made about teaching in Korea, not much has happened... I had to stop my job search as I couldn't get a hold of my documents in time and the timing was just not right. Now I finally secured a job, and I'm leaving for Korea in less than 3 weeks!!

This video is episode two of my 'teaching in Korea' series, in which I give you guys some info on my journey to finding a teaching job. In this video I talk about my experience with hagwon interviews, some questions you may get asked, and some questions you should ask your interviewers! 

Timestamps 
00:00 An update on my journey 
03:06 Waiting for an interview 
05:49 Questions hagwons may ask 
09:39 Questions you should ask in your interview 
21:21 Waiting for a contract 

Teaching in Korea: Episode One https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SqtvXoLCTPQ&t=325s

TAKE THESE WITH A GRAIN OF SALT. Based on personal experiences. Take them how you will. 
The hagwon blacklist https://blacklist.tokyojon.com/
The hagwon greenlist http://greenlist.tokyojon.com/

The Korean Labour standards acts:  
https://elaw.klri.re.kr/eng_service/lawView.do?hseq=25437&lang=ENG

I missed quite a few questions in this video so here are a list of some more you could ask . 
- Ask about the curriculum
- Ask about text books
- Ask about how long classes are
- Ask about a typical day of a teacher at the school 
- Ask about whether you get lesson plans 
- Ask about your salary 
- ALSO ASK FOR CURRENT TEACHERS CONTACTS!!!

#hagwon #teachinginkorea #ESL
